{"word":"ἐμπελάζω","slug":"ἐμπελάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐμπελάζω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>σω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐν'><el>ἐν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to bring near</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to come near, approach</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, like <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to approach</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}